The specific focus on planar graphs suggests cs.CG as a likely category. The paper also mentions the construction of a graph containing all planar graphs as induced subgraphs, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT). The use of label length and bit strings suggests a possible connection to coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions the generalization of the scheme to graphs of bounded Euler genus, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
